race.description: Movie Night @ Southside Cranbourne 10 Jan Handicap
race.comment: Sticking with POWER CABLE (2) who is in great form winning two of three this time in and the unplaced run was good as well. Retains the claim with winning apprentice back aboard and expected to be tough to hold out. BRULLEN (4) has been a long time between drinks but so close lately. Rolled along in front and beaten a nose last time. Can go one better.  LONG BREW (9) resumed from a break at Seymour over 1200m and found the line strongly. Extra trip looks a plus and blinkers go on. Will be running into the finish. COSMIC CHARGER (8) ran a better race last start, finishing 4.5 lengths away in fifth over 1200m at this track. Has placed 3/4 this trip. Likely improver with strong top-three prospects. ROYAL TURF (6) won on debut then was only fair in heavy ground before a break. Fitter for recent jump-outs and has plenty of upside on first campaign.
